00:28:44,144 --> 00:28:47,355
When you're facing a predator,
it's better to hide than run.

271
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:48,607
Why are you so reckless?

272
00:28:49,608 --> 00:28:51,485
I didn't know that.

273
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:54,488
I've always been a predator myself.

274
00:28:58,784 --> 00:29:01,828
The money you wired to Jang Han-seok
will be used for a good cause.

275
00:29:06,833 --> 00:29:10,003
It's been intercepted and sent
to a place that needs it.

276
00:29:26,186 --> 00:29:29,773
You've made a fool of me
on so many levels.

277
00:29:32,275 --> 00:29:34,486
That's my number-one specialty,

278
00:29:35,153 --> 00:29:36,446
next to killing.

279
00:29:38,365 --> 00:29:39,741
Let me just finish this.

280
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:41,409
Then you can kill me.

281
00:29:49,292 --> 00:29:50,460
Aren't you…

282
00:29:53,255 --> 00:29:55,173
more of a Zumba person than a beer person?

283
00:29:56,466 --> 00:29:57,425
Right?

284
00:30:03,682 --> 00:30:04,558
I will…

285
00:30:06,601 --> 00:30:08,019
let you dance all you want.

286
00:30:13,567 --> 00:30:16,361
So Ms. Choi, the CEO of Wusang,
was abducted in that car?

287
00:30:16,444 --> 00:30:19,906
Yes. Her guards who were on standby
in the parking lot reported it.

288
00:30:19,990 --> 00:30:21,116
Who are the abductors?

289
00:30:21,199 --> 00:30:23,118
One of them hasn't been identified,

290
00:30:23,201 --> 00:30:25,453
but the other is Vincenzo Cassano,

291
00:30:26,162 --> 00:30:27,747
a member of the Italian Mafia.

292
00:30:28,248 --> 00:30:30,333
-Why would a Mafia member…
-I'm not sure.

293
00:30:30,417 --> 00:30:31,960
Anyway, Ms. Choi is the attorney

294
00:30:32,043 --> 00:30:35,088
for Jang Han-seok
who is currently on the run.

295
00:30:35,839 --> 00:30:39,509
And the late Han Seung-hyuk
was the former CEO of Wusang.

296
00:30:40,176 --> 00:30:44,097
There's something fishy about it.
They must be related in some way.

297
00:30:44,180 --> 00:30:47,601
Put out an APB on the Mafia member
and track him down along with Jang.

298
00:30:47,684 --> 00:30:50,687
Also, secure footage from Namdongbu
and Ms. Choi's apartment.

299
00:30:50,770 --> 00:30:51,938
Yes, sir.

300
00:31:25,013 --> 00:31:27,891
Don't even try to stand up.
It'll only add to the pain.

301
00:31:32,896 --> 00:31:34,064
Kill me already.

302
00:31:35,148 --> 00:31:36,358
Stop messing around.

303
00:31:42,948 --> 00:31:45,867
What are you going to do with me next?

304
00:31:45,951 --> 00:31:49,621
I told you.
I won't let you die comfortably.

305
00:31:50,789 --> 00:31:53,959
What difference does it make
if you kill me?

306
00:31:54,709 --> 00:31:57,587
Think about it.
Will it bring peace to the world?

307
00:31:58,338 --> 00:32:01,341
Or will it leave a meaningful message?

308
00:32:02,384 --> 00:32:03,468
No way.

309
00:32:04,344 --> 00:32:06,763
It makes no difference whatsoever.

310
00:32:07,514 --> 00:32:12,560
Like you said, I'm just a scumbag
who was killed by another scumbag.

311
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:20,235
No matter how cleverly you kill me,

312
00:32:21,903 --> 00:32:25,532
you're a scumbag like me all the same.

313
00:32:26,533 --> 00:32:27,659
Not at all.

314
00:32:28,827 --> 00:32:29,953
How so?

315
00:32:30,912 --> 00:32:32,580
I'd love to hear how.

316
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,710
I am Vaisravana

317
00:32:37,627 --> 00:32:39,170
who leads yakshas and rakshasas.

318
00:32:39,254 --> 00:32:40,922
What are you talking about?

319
00:32:45,093 --> 00:32:45,969
Are you joking?

320
00:32:47,429 --> 00:32:50,724
It seems like our conversation is
making you less afraid of death.

321
00:33:26,843 --> 00:33:28,928
Don't tell me this is…

322
00:33:38,063 --> 00:33:41,816
You'll feel an intense pain
from beginning to end.

323
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:42,942
No.

324
00:33:43,818 --> 00:33:46,905
You're going way too far.
Don't you think so, Vincenzo?

325
00:33:46,988 --> 00:33:51,117
This isn't right. Didn't you say
you never harm women and children?

326
00:33:51,201 --> 00:33:53,244
To me, you're not a woman.

327
00:33:54,245 --> 00:33:55,538
You're just a monster…

328
00:33:58,041 --> 00:33:59,250
driven by desires.

329
00:34:00,627 --> 00:34:02,670
No.

330
00:34:03,171 --> 00:34:05,924
This isn't right. There are other ways.

331
00:34:06,007 --> 00:34:07,133
Use a gun.

332
00:34:07,217 --> 00:34:09,886
Shoot me. Just shoot me!

333
00:34:09,969 --> 00:34:11,054
Shoot me!

334
00:34:13,932 --> 00:34:16,309
No, no. I'm sorry.

335
00:34:16,392 --> 00:34:18,770
Get back here!

336
00:34:20,063 --> 00:34:21,356
Vincenzo!

337
00:35:13,158 --> 00:35:15,076
Mr. An, do we have a signal on Jang?

338
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:17,245
Yes, we have him again.

339
00:35:17,954 --> 00:35:20,123
He's heading towards the Seobu Expressway.

340
00:35:20,206 --> 00:35:22,167
It's far from where you are,

341
00:35:22,750 --> 00:35:24,752
so I've sent a team to follow him.

342
00:35:24,836 --> 00:35:26,087
I'll catch up soon.

343
00:35:26,171 --> 00:35:28,673
Tell them to be careful
because Jang Han-seok has a gun.

344
00:35:28,756 --> 00:35:30,925
And the police have put out an APB on you.

345
00:35:31,551 --> 00:35:33,720
So you should move quickly.

346
00:35:34,304 --> 00:35:35,805
I understand.

347
00:35:44,230 --> 00:35:47,358
He's getting farther and farther away.
Step on it!

348
00:35:47,442 --> 00:35:49,569
I'm going as fast as I can.

349
00:35:49,652 --> 00:35:51,404
There's too many people. That's why.

350
00:35:51,487 --> 00:35:53,823
That's ridiculous.
This isn't a cultivator.

351
00:35:54,741 --> 00:35:56,576
We were in second gear. Sorry.

352
00:35:56,659 --> 00:35:58,578
-Gosh!
-Seriously!

353
00:35:58,661 --> 00:35:59,954
Damn it.

354
00:36:00,038 --> 00:36:01,414
Let me switch to third gear.

355
00:36:01,497 --> 00:36:03,082
We're going to lose him!

356
00:36:03,166 --> 00:36:05,293
-Third. Good now?
-Good.

357
00:36:05,376 --> 00:36:06,753
Good. Here we go. Third gear.

358
00:36:06,836 --> 00:36:08,963
Switching to fourth gear.

359
00:36:31,069 --> 00:36:34,280
Look at you guys. Why are you so down?

360
00:36:34,364 --> 00:36:36,866
This isn't right for a chairman
of a conglomerate.

361
00:36:37,450 --> 00:36:38,785
-How embarrassing.
-All right.

362
00:36:38,868 --> 00:36:41,496
Let's get it on by the sea!

363
00:37:16,114 --> 00:37:19,701
Don't resist.
You'll only be choked even harder.

364
00:37:29,252 --> 00:37:32,672
Stop it, you bastard! That's enough!

365
00:37:32,755 --> 00:37:33,756
Put down the knife!

366
00:37:36,926 --> 00:37:37,969
-Mr. Lee!
-Mr. Lee!

367
00:38:08,916 --> 00:38:10,418
-Mr. Lee!
-Mr. Lee!

368
00:38:10,501 --> 00:38:12,754
Mr. Lee! What should we do?

369
00:38:12,837 --> 00:38:14,213
-Call 911 right now.
-Okay.

370
00:38:14,797 --> 00:38:15,673
Hang in there.

371
00:38:15,757 --> 00:38:17,467
Help will arrive soon.

372
00:38:17,550 --> 00:38:19,635
Hello? Is this 911?

373
00:38:19,719 --> 00:38:22,388
I'm calling from Geumjo Port.

374
00:38:23,514 --> 00:38:26,726
Someone has been stabbed. Please hurry.

375
00:38:26,809 --> 00:38:28,144
That son of a bitch.

376
00:38:35,818 --> 00:38:37,820
Mr. Lee.

377
00:38:39,781 --> 00:38:40,907
We caught him…

378
00:38:41,991 --> 00:38:42,867
right?

379
00:38:44,744 --> 00:38:45,787
Yes, we did.

380
00:38:47,330 --> 00:38:49,624
Don't hand him over to the police.

381
00:38:50,708 --> 00:38:54,170
Make sure to punish him yourself.

382
00:38:56,547 --> 00:38:59,050
Okay. Don't talk anymore.

383
00:39:00,593 --> 00:39:02,512
Once Dal-rae…

384
00:39:04,263 --> 00:39:05,390
is born,

385
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:08,226
I wanted…

386
00:39:09,769 --> 00:39:15,024
to ask you to be her godfather.

387
00:39:17,693 --> 00:39:18,569
Okay.

388
00:39:19,529 --> 00:39:22,407
I'll do that. I'll be her godfather.

389
00:39:23,533 --> 00:39:24,617
You…

390
00:39:26,077 --> 00:39:29,622
You promised. Keep your promise.

391
00:39:32,417 --> 00:39:33,668
Okay?

392
00:39:37,380 --> 00:39:39,424
Of course.

393
00:39:40,633 --> 00:39:41,634
I will.

394
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:43,803
Thank…

395
00:39:45,179 --> 00:39:46,431
Thank you.

396
00:39:49,517 --> 00:39:50,560
Mr. Lee.

397
00:39:51,394 --> 00:39:52,228
Mr. Lee.

398
00:39:53,980 --> 00:39:55,022
Mr. Lee.

399
00:39:55,773 --> 00:39:56,899
Hurry!

400
00:39:57,483 --> 00:39:58,568
Let me help him.

401
00:39:59,235 --> 00:40:00,820
Mr. Lee, raise your right leg.

402
00:40:01,487 --> 00:40:04,157
-I'll raise it, okay?
-Mr. Lee, don't close your eyes.

403
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,450
Hang in there.

404
00:40:05,533 --> 00:40:07,285
What should we do?

405
00:40:07,368 --> 00:40:08,202
No!

406
00:40:08,286 --> 00:40:09,787
Don't touch it.

407
00:40:09,871 --> 00:40:11,998
-Never.
-Do you even know what you're doing?

408
00:40:12,081 --> 00:40:15,084
I used to be a surgical nurse.
The White Angel of Geumga-dong!

409
00:40:16,294 --> 00:40:18,379
Hang in there. Don't talk to me.

410
00:40:27,555 --> 00:40:29,182
Almost done. Hang in there.

411
00:40:36,898 --> 00:40:39,609
That's not 911. It's the police.

412
00:41:04,342 --> 00:41:05,801
See you again, Consigliere.

413
00:41:06,886 --> 00:41:08,054
Thank you for everything.

414
00:41:09,055 --> 00:41:10,056
Be safe.

415
00:41:15,061 --> 00:41:16,562
Go on, now.

416
00:41:17,980 --> 00:41:19,023
Go.

417
00:41:46,384 --> 00:41:49,470
Stop the SUV. We'll fire if you don't.

418
00:41:50,137 --> 00:41:53,099
Stop the SUV. We'll fire if you don't.

419
00:42:01,023 --> 00:42:02,942
-What are you doing?
-We have a patient.

420
00:42:03,025 --> 00:42:04,777
-Move your car!
-What are you doing?

421
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:07,029
-Move it.
-We have a patient here!

422
00:42:07,113 --> 00:42:08,531
Move your car!

423
00:42:08,614 --> 00:42:10,366
-Move it!
-Someone's hurt.

424
00:42:25,131 --> 00:42:26,173
Okay.

425
00:42:33,222 --> 00:42:34,890
He escaped safely.

426
00:42:38,269 --> 00:42:41,689
And he has Chairman Jang with him.

427
00:42:43,733 --> 00:42:45,901
Things will finally come to an end.

428
00:42:51,532 --> 00:42:52,658
Ms. Hong.

429
00:42:57,705 --> 00:42:59,373
Mr. Lee is…

430
00:43:06,672 --> 00:43:08,716
What about him?

431
00:44:04,313 --> 00:44:05,981
How did you find me?

432
00:44:08,067 --> 00:44:09,568
Your brother told me.

433
00:44:10,820 --> 00:44:11,737
What?

434
00:44:15,658 --> 00:44:18,327
Hey, do you want to hear
something interesting?

435
00:44:20,413 --> 00:44:22,331
On the morning of the inauguration,

436
00:44:22,415 --> 00:44:25,376
Han-seok suddenly gave me a watch
as a gift.

437
00:44:25,459 --> 00:44:26,377
Okay.

438
00:44:27,086 --> 00:44:28,921
And matching watches at that.

439
00:44:29,505 --> 00:44:31,048
He's not the type to do that.

440
00:44:36,011 --> 00:44:39,890
So I found it suspicious
and disassembled it.

441
00:44:43,060 --> 00:44:44,270
Guess what I found.

442
00:44:45,104 --> 00:44:47,898
An expert said that it was a tracker.

443
00:44:48,524 --> 00:44:51,068
A tracker? So what did you do?

444
00:44:51,569 --> 00:44:53,737
I put it in his watch without his knowing.

445
00:44:55,531 --> 00:44:56,866
And I didn't wear mine.

446
00:44:57,616 --> 00:45:02,997
Also, I downloaded an app
that can track him whenever I want.

447
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:05,583
It was quite expensive. Was I ripped off?

448
00:45:07,877 --> 00:45:09,211
But why are you tracking him?

449
00:45:10,421 --> 00:45:13,132
I'm certain that
he'll do something horrible again soon.

450
00:45:13,716 --> 00:45:15,593
Then he'll run away like always.

451
00:45:16,093 --> 00:45:18,721
Even when he killed his friends
in middle school,

452
00:45:18,804 --> 00:45:21,348
my father sent him away
so no one could find him.

453
00:45:23,851 --> 00:45:25,519
Had he been punished then,

454
00:45:26,770 --> 00:45:28,606
he may not have turned out this way.

455
00:45:33,694 --> 00:45:36,822
But doesn't he change watches every day?
What's the use?

456
00:45:36,906 --> 00:45:38,949
That's why I put trackers in all of them.

457
00:45:39,867 --> 00:45:42,661
-What?
-I tend to be foolish like that.

458
00:45:50,544 --> 00:45:52,588
In the end, he was right.

459
00:45:56,634 --> 00:46:00,137
He's damn useless until the very end.

460
00:46:08,646 --> 00:46:09,522
By the way,

461
00:46:11,732 --> 00:46:13,192
what is this toy?

462
00:46:19,031 --> 00:46:22,660
I learned it from the Russian Mafia
when I visited Russia.

463
00:46:24,286 --> 00:46:26,080
It's called kop'yo iskuplen'ya.

464
00:46:31,794 --> 00:46:33,295
"The spear of atonement."

465
00:46:44,306 --> 00:46:46,308
Do you really think
I'll atone for my sins?

466
00:46:46,392 --> 00:46:48,811
I couldn't care less.

467
00:46:49,812 --> 00:46:51,981
As long as you're in pain, I'm happy.

468
00:46:52,064 --> 00:46:54,233
You should've just killed me
back at the port.

469
00:46:54,900 --> 00:46:56,860
I always keep my word.

470
00:46:59,655 --> 00:47:02,449
Do you remember everything
I've told you until now?

471
00:47:11,625 --> 00:47:12,710
Wait.

472
00:47:13,961 --> 00:47:16,297
I'm glad you seem to remember.

473
00:47:22,678 --> 00:47:24,597
What is this?

474
00:47:34,189 --> 00:47:38,360
The spear of atonement
will pierce by 5mm every 5 minutes.

475
00:47:38,444 --> 00:47:41,071
You'll feel lightheaded
from all the blood loss,

476
00:47:41,155 --> 00:47:42,781
and feel excruciating pain.

477
00:47:44,908 --> 00:47:46,160
Around tomorrow noon,

478
00:47:47,453 --> 00:47:50,164
it'll pierce your lung,
and you'll die instantly.

479
00:47:52,082 --> 00:47:53,417
Vincenzo.

480
00:47:55,169 --> 00:47:57,171
Aren't we both businessmen?

481
00:47:57,880 --> 00:47:59,840
I have many great offers to make.

482
00:48:00,424 --> 00:48:03,594
You don't need to resort
to such barbaric acts!

483
00:48:03,677 --> 00:48:05,971
-Please.
-Barbaric acts?

484
00:48:06,805 --> 00:48:07,890
Yes.

485
00:48:11,143 --> 00:48:14,355
This world has always been barbaric.

486
00:48:18,400 --> 00:48:20,778
I'll give you all the money I have.

487
00:48:20,861 --> 00:48:21,945
So, please…

488
00:48:22,571 --> 00:48:24,448
If that's not enough,

489
00:48:24,531 --> 00:48:27,034
you can cut off one of my limbs.

490
00:48:27,618 --> 00:48:30,120
Sparing me isn't that difficult, right?

491
00:48:30,913 --> 00:48:32,206
It's not.

492
00:48:34,291 --> 00:48:35,751
But I don't want to.

493
00:48:46,720 --> 00:48:49,014
It hasn't been five minutes yet!

494
00:48:51,475 --> 00:48:53,143
I've controlled it manually for now.

495
00:48:54,103 --> 00:48:55,646
I'll switch it back to auto.

496
00:48:57,481 --> 00:49:00,025
Vincenzo. Please.

497
00:49:01,026 --> 00:49:03,153
Vincenzo, this isn't you.

498
00:49:05,531 --> 00:49:07,449
Just shoot me in the head, okay?

499
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:10,619
Just shoot me! Shoot!

500
00:49:11,286 --> 00:49:13,706
Please… Vincenzo.

501
00:49:13,789 --> 00:49:15,416
Go apologize to your brother.

502
00:49:22,214 --> 00:49:23,757
Please…

503
00:49:23,841 --> 00:49:25,718
I'll keep this as a trophy.

504
00:49:28,053 --> 00:49:28,929
Vincenzo…

505
00:49:29,930 --> 00:49:30,764
Vincenzo.

506
00:49:32,266 --> 00:49:33,475
Hey!

507
00:49:34,810 --> 00:49:37,271
Just shoot me! Kill me now!

508
00:49:54,955 --> 00:49:58,125
LAWYER HONG CHA-YOUNG

509
00:50:03,213 --> 00:50:05,424
LAWYER HONG CHA-YOUNG

510
00:50:21,106 --> 00:50:23,358
POWER OFF

511
00:51:05,442 --> 00:51:06,735
I'm sorry I'm late.

512
00:51:06,819 --> 00:51:08,904
I've lured the investigation team
to Busan.

513
00:51:09,404 --> 00:51:10,948
Here. It's a Korean passport.

514
00:51:12,366 --> 00:51:14,451
You must board within the next 30 minutes.

515
00:51:14,535 --> 00:51:17,287
Until then, your background check
and face recognition

516
00:51:17,371 --> 00:51:19,289
will be linked to that photo.

517
00:51:19,373 --> 00:51:22,793
After 30 minutes,
the data will be linked to you, so hurry.

518
00:51:23,836 --> 00:51:25,128
Thank you.

519
00:51:25,212 --> 00:51:28,507
You should thank Director Tae, not us.

520
00:51:28,590 --> 00:51:31,093
I see. Please tell him I said thank you.

521
00:51:31,677 --> 00:51:32,845
If you can't come back…

522
00:51:36,348 --> 00:51:38,517
do give us a call someday.

523
00:51:41,895 --> 00:51:43,021
Thank you,

524
00:51:43,105 --> 00:51:44,189
Let's go.

525
00:52:11,508 --> 00:52:12,426
Mr. Cassano.

526
00:52:16,388 --> 00:52:17,681
You shouldn't move around.

527
00:52:17,764 --> 00:52:18,974
I'm okay.

528
00:52:20,392 --> 00:52:22,019
I'm glad I got to see you.

529
00:52:22,853 --> 00:52:24,146
You should go now.

530
00:52:24,813 --> 00:52:27,316
There will be a lot of headaches for you
after I leave.

531
00:52:28,317 --> 00:52:29,735
I can handle that.

532
00:52:52,549 --> 00:52:53,842
Goodbye.

533
00:53:00,390 --> 00:53:01,934
Be safe.

534
00:53:05,020 --> 00:53:05,896
I'll get going.

535
00:53:07,439 --> 00:53:08,649
Hurry.

