Right. This too.

796
01:13:03,592 --> 01:13:04,677
What is this?

797
01:13:11,600 --> 01:13:14,895
CELEBRATION OF KOREA AND ITALY'S
DIPLOMATIC RELATIONS

798
01:13:14,979 --> 01:13:16,355
Do you want to go with me tomorrow?

799
01:13:16,439 --> 01:13:21,444
But I'll be attending
a paper airplane competition tomorrow.

800
01:13:21,527 --> 01:13:22,778
See?

801
01:13:26,782 --> 01:13:28,451
You can do it, Edward.

802
01:13:29,827 --> 01:13:30,661
Good.

803
01:13:34,331 --> 01:13:35,374
I see.

804
01:13:49,847 --> 01:13:52,766
CELEBRATION OF KOREA AND ITALY'S
DIPLOMATIC RELATIONS

805
01:14:04,904 --> 01:14:07,364
It's been a while, Ambassador Sponza.

806
01:14:27,009 --> 01:14:29,428
War and art are best observed
from a distance.

807
01:14:55,538 --> 01:14:57,498
Good evening, miss.

808
01:15:06,382 --> 01:15:07,466
Have you been well?

809
01:15:14,723 --> 01:15:16,141
How did you get here?

810
01:15:17,935 --> 01:15:20,062
I sneaked in with the Italian delegation.

811
01:15:21,438 --> 01:15:22,648
I'll be leaving tomorrow.

812
01:15:27,570 --> 01:15:29,905
Are you only able to come
during an event like this?

813
01:15:31,407 --> 01:15:33,576
Yes. Just for a day.

814
01:15:35,452 --> 01:15:36,328
But…

815
01:15:39,832 --> 01:15:41,292
I'll invite you to my island.

816
01:15:45,087 --> 01:15:46,088
Your island?

817
01:15:50,009 --> 01:15:51,802
You mean the island in the postcard?

818
01:16:05,566 --> 01:16:08,277
I bought a deserted island near Malta.

819
01:16:08,944 --> 01:16:11,780
I named it myself as well. Pagliuzza.

820
01:16:12,823 --> 01:16:14,575
In Korean, it means "straws."

821
01:16:17,911 --> 01:16:20,247
You must've spent all your money on that.

822
01:16:20,789 --> 01:16:22,082
I have a bit left.

823
01:16:24,835 --> 01:16:27,087
Thanks for letting me hide the gold.

824
01:16:27,630 --> 01:16:31,258
I was truly relieved
that you had that spot in your house.

825
01:18:21,577 --> 01:18:23,245
Is that where you're living?

826
01:18:23,871 --> 01:18:24,955
Yes.

827
01:18:25,539 --> 01:18:27,499
The Cassano family settled there.

828
01:18:27,583 --> 01:18:28,792
In secret, of course.

829
01:18:29,376 --> 01:18:30,794
Are you their boss now?

830
01:18:35,424 --> 01:18:37,509
You're a boss now, not a consigliere?

831
01:18:42,097 --> 01:18:43,515
The island has many purposes.

832
01:18:44,808 --> 01:18:46,977
It's a refuge for exhausted fighters,

833
01:18:47,728 --> 01:18:51,857
a hideout for your loved ones,
and a place of healing.

834
01:18:53,358 --> 01:18:54,568
Can I go there as well?

835
01:18:55,360 --> 01:18:56,403
Yes.

836
01:18:57,780 --> 01:18:59,656
I've set aside a room for you.

837
01:19:01,909 --> 01:19:02,993
No way.

838
01:19:03,577 --> 01:19:04,912
I can't wait to go there.

839
01:19:18,550 --> 01:19:19,968
I've missed you a lot.

840
01:19:24,348 --> 01:19:25,516
Me too.

841
01:19:27,392 --> 01:19:31,063
You've always been on my mind
ever since I left.

842
01:19:33,857 --> 01:19:35,108
That's hard to believe.

843
01:20:17,526 --> 01:20:18,694
Do you believe me now?

844
01:20:22,030 --> 01:20:25,033
Villains never break up
because they're tenacious…

845
01:20:27,077 --> 01:20:28,662
even when they love.

846
01:22:23,485 --> 01:22:27,823
Two days ago, I used three Luciano
family members as manure for the vineyard

847
01:22:27,906 --> 01:22:30,909
and took over the olive plantations
in Malta.

848
01:22:32,703 --> 01:22:35,998
I'm still a villain
and couldn't care less about justice.

849
01:22:36,873 --> 01:22:38,709
Justice is weak and empty.

850
01:22:41,336 --> 01:22:43,922
One cannot win against any villains
with justice alone.

851
01:22:45,048 --> 01:22:47,676
If merciless justice exists,

852
01:22:48,260 --> 01:22:50,220
I am willing to yield to it.

853
01:22:51,805 --> 01:22:55,142
Even villains long to live
in a peaceful world.

854
01:22:56,685 --> 01:23:00,188
However, since that's impossible,
I've taken up a new hobby.

855
01:23:01,231 --> 01:23:02,649
Getting rid of garbage.

856
01:23:03,483 --> 01:23:06,945
If I don't do that, people will die
buried underneath the garbage.

857
01:23:11,742 --> 01:23:15,120
There's one last thing I'd like to say
from a villain's perspective.

858
01:23:19,041 --> 01:23:20,292
Evil is…

859
01:23:20,834 --> 01:23:23,128
prevalen and vehement.

860
01:23:41,146 --> 01:23:43,356
SPECIAL THANKS TO CHA SOON-BAE,
KIM SUNG-CHEOL, AND JEON GUK-HYANG

861
01:27:18,655 --> 01:27:19,948
THE END

862
